==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bocking
<hw>Bock"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A coarse woolen fabric, used for
floor cloths, to cover carpets, etc.; -- so called from the town of
<etsep>Bocking</etsep>, in England, where it was first made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bockland</ent>⟦br⟧
